## 4. Cross-cutting concerns

### 4.1 Seed integration with `app.module.ts`

`CurrenciesSeed` must be added to `providers[]` in `app.module.ts` like `UnitsSeed`, `CategoriesSeed`, `WarehouseSeed` (already imported, ordering matters: `StatusesSeed → OrgRolesSeed → CounterpartyRolesSeed → UnitsSeed → CategoriesSeed → WarehouseSeed → CurrenciesSeed`). No cross-seed dependency; can run in any order.

### 4.2 Permissions / RBAC

All new controllers MUST add `@Roles(...)` decorators consistent with neighboring controllers (`UnitController.list` = `admin,manager,user`; `ProductModuleController.list` = `admin,manager`). The `RolesGuard` global guard in `app.module.ts` will enforce and 403-deny untagged calls.

### 4.3 Audit logging

`AuditAction` decorator on POST/PATCH/DELETE mirrors `UnitController` (`action: 'create' | 'update' | 'delete'`, `entityType: 'Currency'` / `'ProductModule'`). `AuditInterceptor` is global; nothing to register.

### 4.4 Inventory summary strongly-typed DTO

Create `backend/src/modules/inventory/dto/inventory-summary.dto.ts` — top-level interface per §3.C. Avoid `any` in controller return. (Plain TS interface is OK; no class-validator needed for read-only response.)

### 4.5 No frontend / kit additions

TZ-102 is backend-only. Frontend swap for sub-task B is a 1-line URL change in an existing service; no new component. Frontend **does not** get `/currencies` or `/inventory` pages in this TZ — those are TZ-103+.

---

