## 7. Edge cases & risks

### 7.1 Currency RBAC over-sharing
`CurrencyController.list` mirrors `UnitController.list` (`admin,manager,user`). This is **permissive GET** to enable future form dropdowns. If TZ-43 requires tighter CRL (rate must be admin-only), add `if (req.user.role !== 'admin' && method !== 'GET')` early. Post-TZ-102 concern.

### 7.2 Currency seed race
`CurrenciesSeed` runs on `OnApplicationBootstrap`. If dropped / recreated on a Mongo with stale `currencies` collection, the `findByKey`-then-`create` pattern (as in `UnitsSeed`) handles idempotency. **Mirror `UnitsSeed` exact pattern** — try `findByKey`, fallback to `create`, catch errors per-row. Never wipe.

### 7.3 Inventory summary perf under large data
Mongo `$facet` aggregation is bounded (counts only top-N). At 100k storage-items, `$count` is O(n) but `totalActiveItems` is single index-scan (`{isActive:1,qty:1}`). Test with 10k items synthetic — expect <500 ms. If it ever fails perf budget (SLA TODO), move to materialised view (TZ-103+).

### 7.4 `low-stock` can't change
Sub-task C preserves `@Get('low-stock')` exactly as it was. Frontend InventoryDashboardPage currently has `lowStock` card — that path must stay **unchanged**. The new bare `@Get()` adds **above** it, no replacement.

### 7.5 Frontend service file location
The `/api/product-modules → /api/modules` swap needs the ACTUAL frontend service file. `grep -rE "'/api/product-modules'" frontend/src/app --include='*.ts'` returns the file path. If a service uses full URL `http://localhost:3000/api/product-modules`, that string also gets swapped. Confirm BEFORE editing.

### 7.6 Frontend `dataModel` reference
If `frontend/src/app/data-model.ts` or `docs/data-model.md` references the old `/product-modules` URL, update it in the same commit.

### 7.7 StockMovementService / WarehouseService injection risk
`inventory.module.ts` currently imports only `StorageItemModule`. Adding `WarehouseModule` + `StockMovementModule` **must produce a valid Nest DI tree** AND those `.module.ts` files MUST export their respective services (`exports: [WarehouseService]`, `exports: [StockMovementService, MongooseModule]`). NestJS DI will throw `Nest can't resolve dependencies of the InventoryController` at server boot if not. **Preflight:** `cat backend/src/modules/warehouse/warehouse.module.ts | grep exports:` and same for stock-movement before writing `inventory.module.ts`. If exports are missing, edit both caller AND callee modules in the same commit.

Both modules already exist in `app.module.ts` imports — won't conflict at app-module level. Note in commit body.

### 7.8 Scope creep guard
TZ-102 does NOT include:
- Currency exchange-rate refresh job (post-TZ-43)
- TZ-103 inventory dashboard frontend page (out of scope for THIS TZ)
- `/api/modules/:id` rewrite (already exists; no change needed)
- Currencies in side-nav (post-TZ-43)

